      "term": "capsids",
      "kind": "word",
      "cefrLevel": "null",
      "senses": [
        {
          "pos": "noun (plural of capsid)",
          "definition": "the protein shell that encloses the genetic material of a virus",
          "examples": [
            "Viruses have a protective capsids made of protein subunits.",
            "Researchers studied variations in capsids to understand viral stability."
